Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Library Technician, Public Services Castlegar , BC Description Main Duties and ResponsibilitiesPerforms circulation duties in support of the Library’s public service operations including:Charging and discharging materials, performing renewals, holds and item updates using the integrated library system (ILS);Registering new patrons and producing photo identification cards for students and staff;Managing Reserves collectionShelving materials and maintaining correct order of materials on shelves;Providing general orientation, direction and instruction to library patrons; Maintaining and demonstrating peripheral equipment to patrons (copiers, printers, scanners, microfilm reader, etc.);Maintaining equipment lending pool by ensuring laptops, projectors, are in good working order;Performs other related duties as assigned by supervisor.Skills, Knowledge and AbilitiesAbility to work proficiently with Integrated Library System (ILS) software.Proficiency with Microsoft OfficeExcellent interpersonal skillsExcellent critical thinking skillsAbility to work in a multi-tasking environmentExcellent customer service skillsGood physical conditionEducation and ExperienceLibrary Technician Diploma, or currently enrolled in a Library Technician program.Library experience, preferably in an academic library.This is a regular, full-time (100%) position commencing August 26, 2024. Salary will be Pay Grade 6 - $29.86 per hour in accordance with the PPWC Collective Agreement.Full posting:https://careers.selkirk.ca/vacancy/library-technic... Compensation $29.86 per hour Closes: 19 August, 2024 Selkirk College Castlegar , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
