Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Program &amp; Outreach Coordinator Lanark , ON Description Status: Part-time, PermanentEmployee Group: Non-Management/Non UnionReports to: CEOPay band: D ; $26.93-$31.69 (2024 rates)Hours of work: 20 hours per week, includes 1 regular evening/week and 2 Saturdays/monthAdditional Hours of Work (Temporary): additional 9 hours a week secured for Sept 2024 – Mar 2025 Position Summary Lanark Highlands Public Library initiates contact with community groups and members through active outreach and programming and offers a wide range of programs for customers of all ages. The Program &amp; Outreach Coordinator is responsible for the planning and development of programming for all ages, including implementation and evaluation in accordance with Board policy and in coordination with the Chief Executive Officer (CEO). Responsibilities The individual is a customer service champion first and foremost; in addition, is responsible for the following duties: Participates in front-line customer service by actively working shifts on the library service desks.Strategically responds to the need for specific programs and events in coordination with the CEOCreate children’s displays ensuring engaging and relevant displays on a regular basisWrites content for the Library webpage, newsletter and other marketing materialEnsures high standards of library services by analyzing records and statistics for circulation, program attendance and other library activities Assist in sourcing funding opportunities to execute programsWhen working alone, contacts CEO/Chief Librarian, in case of emergency Plans, delivers and evaluates programs, workshops, special events and presentations for all ages Initiates and pursues program partnerships with community organizations and individuals; acts as a community/library liaison Participates in community events and meetings in coordination with the CEO In coordination with the CEO, uses the library branding to promote programs and events through various media outlets Maintains, publishes and submits related records, statistics and evaluations as required Utilize programming and outreach activities to promote additional programs, services and collections Tracks revenues and expenditures within the allocated programming budget in coordination with the CEO Other duties as required Skills &amp; Competencies Effective written and oral communication skillsDisplays excellent interpersonal and team-oriented workplace skillsWorking knowledge of ILS systems, Microsoft Office software, social media platforms, CanvaAptitude for organization with attention to detail and accuracy; maintains confidentialityExperience in a public service setting, preferably in a public library environmentAbility to establish and maintain effective working relationships with community groups, external agencies and the general public. Excellent communication, organizational and interpersonal skillsRelevant undergraduate degree or approved equivalent combination of education and experience; public library experience is an assetValid Driver’s License (class G)2 years of proven excellence in programming and outreach including customer serviceExperience working with children Ability to multi-task on a daily basis Qualifications Working Relationships: Internal Library Staff, CEO, Municipal Staff External Library Patrons, Community Partners, Local Elementary Schools Working Conditions Constant interaction with the general public Evening and weekend service desk/program shifts required Requires travel within the community Position requires lifting – 20lbs+ ; shoveling snow Physical demand requires a high positive energy level, computer usage, sitting, standing, bending, and lifting Working conditions are conducted in a library environment, also includes conditions outside the library environment in various community settings, with exposure to public interaction, questions and concerns Multi-tasking is required on a daily basis At times works alone evening, weekends and occasionally midweek. Compensation $26.93-$31.69 (2024 rates) Closes: 23 August, 2024 Lanark Highlands Public Library Lanark , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
