Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? STUDENT LIBRARIAN TECHNOLOGY AND YOUTH DEPARTMENT (LIBRARY ASSISTANT III) - Casual – 2 positions) West Vancouver , BC Description Located on the traditional, ancestral and unceded lands of the Musqueam, Squamish, and Tsleil-Waututh Nations, West Vancouver is a vibrant community on the North Shore and home to parks, beaches, and to sports, recreation and arts amenities. We are seeking employees with a passion for public service who share our commitment to creating a complete, inclusive and livable community. Our dedicated staff deliver services, operate facilities and run the programs that enhance the well-being of our community.The West Vancouver Memorial Library has an opening for a Student Librarian to work on two teams: Digital Experience (Technology) and Youth. This is an exciting opportunity for someone passionate about public libraries to work with both kids and adults, with a focus on seniors.Both departments are driven, inspired, and known throughout the province for innovation, responsiveness, and leadership. Reporting to the Digital Experience Coordinator - duties will include, but are not limited to (with assistance from a Librarian):Assisting patrons with new technologies to meet a variety of information needs at the Community Computing Centre (CCC) public service desk and / orAssisting kids and families with reader’s advisory and reference at the Youth Department public service deskProgramming with an emphasis on middle years (ages 9-12) and adult technology classes. As much as possible, we try to align programs and projects with our Student Librarian’s areas of interest and passion, while also providing new experiences and opportunities to grow their resume.Candidates should be enrolled in SLAIS: the iSchool at UBC or an equivalent program at another educational institution, in their second year of study and pursuing a MLIS degree. Essential requirements are:a passion for customer service and connecting people with online library resources and programsa strong interest in or previous experience with mobile technology, apps and instructional designexcellent communication and interpersonal skillsexperience or interest/comfort working with both kids and seniorsexperience with accessing and downloading digital content (ex: e-books, e-audiobooks)the ability to work well as part of a teamThe majority of this work will be done on-site at the Library on weekdays.The preferred candidate will be available up to 25 hours / week from September to December.The successful candidate will be required to supply an acceptable police information check.This posting does not list all the duties of the position, nor does it fully detail the required skills, knowledge and abilities, licences and certificates required of candidates. For details please refer to the class specification which is available for inspection on WestNet or contact Human Resources to request a copy. Position Status:Union (WVMEA) – CasualHours of Work:Up to 25 hours per week (hours and days of work may vary)Starting Rate of Pay:$27.03 per hour plus 4% in lieu of benefitsClosing Date:11:59 p.m. on August 5, 2024To Apply:Please visit the District of West Vancouver’s Career Centre at westvancouver.ca/careers to apply for this position.We want to thank all applicants, however only those chosen for an interview will be contacted.5530-24-WVMEA-CASUAL-30If you have any questions please contact us at careers@westvancouver.ca Compensation 27.03 per hour plus 4% in lieu of benefits Closes: 5 August, 2024 West Vancouver Memorial Library West Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
